title: Grateful Dead Live at Harpur College on 1970-05-02
description: Set 1 Don't Ease Me In, I Know You Rider, Friend Of The Devil, Dire Wolf, Beat It On Down The Line-> Black Peter, Candyman-> Cumberland Blues, Deep Elem Blues, Cold Jordan*, Uncle John's Band Set 2 Saint Stephen-> Cryptical Envelopement-> Drums-> The Other One-> Cryptical Envelopement-> Cosmic Charlie, Casey Jones, Good Lovin'-> Drums-> Good Lovin', Cold Rain & Snow, It's A Man's World, Dancin' In The Streets Set 3 Morning Dew, Viola Lee Blues-> Feedback-> We Bid You Good Night *with members of NRPS Other artist(s): NRPS. First set acoustic. This date is featured on Dick's Picks 8.

reviews.review_text: Oh My God Greatest show on the face of the planet Even with Mistakes,cuts and sound issues. Massive Massive Massive  Get The Dicks Picks like yesterday
amazing show good ol' wooden grateful dead.   FAT monitors!

Rating: *********************************************** By far my favorite Dick's Picks and the most memorable show for me... and it still amazes me again and again...  BUY OR GET THIS SHOW!  You will not regret it.
Best Dicks Picks ever? And possibly the finest performance of 1970
VLB All I need to say is thank god for VLB.   Every time I hear that song I am taken far away and back again and again and again...  pure joy

What about the NRPS? I read that the NR also played - their performances at this time were also legendary.  Would love to know if their sets were captured anywhere.  For that matter, are there any SB of NRPS from their touring with the Dead?

Thanks - Richard
***** Cryptical Envelopment through Cosmic Charlie is as high as it gets.

"Relax, we have you all night long!" the electrics sets are amazing but its the acoustic set that makes this show so important. 

The acoustic shows from 1970 are some of the greatest American folk music you will ever hear. Its these shows that set the band and Jerry and apart from every other. The musical  virtuosity was unprecedented.. and will most likely forever remain unmatched. 

The official release has set 3 and its absolutely insane! worth pursing

Thats it for the Other One Thats it>cryptical makes my eyes go crossed and my tongue hang out. Ive had this on tape from such a long time ago. This recording is great as most of the stuff I find on archive.org. Cosmic Charlie is the cherry on top.
